--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. PREAMBLE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The Cluaiz Source-Available License (CSL) is designed to cultivate a high-performance,
collaborative ecosystem. By making our source code visible and adaptable, we empower
individual developers, startups, researchers, and hobbyists to build freely. At the 
same time, this license requires fair commercial participation from large-scale 
enterprises and protects the platform from competing hosted clones.

This is a SOURCE-AVAILABLE license. It is NOT an OSI-approved Open Source license.
It offers a balanced "Open-Core" model: completely free for personal, educational, 
startup, and local self-hosted use, with commercial licensing required for large 
enterprises and managed service providers.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. DEFINITIONS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"Licensed Software" means the source code, build scripts, configuration files, 
and documentation of the Cluaiz ecosystem made available under this License.

"Enterprise" means any corporate entity, business, or organization (including 
its parent company, subsidiaries, and controlled affiliates) whose annual gross 
revenue exceeded Ten Million USD ($10,000,000 USD) in its preceding fiscal year.

"Contributor" means any individual or corporate entity that has authored and 
had an accepted merged contribution in the official upstream repository of the 
Licensed Software.

"Competing SaaS / Hosted Service" means any service that provides the core 
functional features of the Licensed Software as a hosted platform, managed API, 
managed container, or cloud offering in direct commercial competition with the 
official cloud services or commercial API endpoints hosted by Cluaiz.

