================================================================================
                      FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS (FAQ)
================================================================================

Q: Is Cluaiz open-source?
A: Cluaiz is "source-available" or "open-core". You have complete access to the 
   source code, and you can compile, modify, and self-host it freely. However, 
   because we restrict competing hosted services and charge enterprises with 
   annual revenue above $10M, it does not meet the strict OSI definition of 
   "open-source".

Q: Can I use Cluaiz commercially?
A: Yes! If your company's annual revenue is under $10M USD, you can use Cluaiz 
   commercially for free. If you exceed this threshold, or if you are active contributors 
   (who get a full waiver), or if you run a competing SaaS, you need a commercial agreement.

Q: Can I fork the repository and make modifications?
A: Absolutely! You can fork, modify, and distribute your changes under this 
   same license, provided you remove all official Cluaiz branding, names, 
   and logos, and do not use the modified version to run a competing SaaS.

Q: Can I build plugins, models, or extensions for Cluaiz?
A: Yes! We highly encourage the community to build plugins, drivers, and 
   extensions. These belong entirely to you and can be licensed under any terms 
   you choose.

Q: Can I self-host Cluaiz on my own infrastructure?
A: Yes. Local deployment and self-hosting for your internal startup/personal 
   use are 100% free and fully supported.